The paper proposes a framework for parallel optimization of a differentiable function and a separable nonsmooth, convex one, which is commonly used in Lasso problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization algorithms for big data, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses theoretical convergence results and numerical experiments, which could also place it in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
